stimulus:
["

During this experiment, you will watch an episode of a publicly broadcasted murder mystery television show.

It contains adult themes and graphic language. While the video will portray a character accused of a violent crime, as well as verbal descriptions of the crime, violence will not be shown, nor will any other graphic visual content.


If you are not comfortable with continuing, please exit this experiment now.



Otherwise, please press the SPACE BAR to continue.

"]

Thank you for agreeing to participate in this experiment!



Please press the SPACE BAR to continue

Before we begin, please be sure that you are in a good space to complete the experiment. This space should be:



Comfortable

Distraction-free

Available for the next 60 minutes




Please press the SPACE BAR to continue

Please give your full attention to the experiment. This includes:



Closing or minimizing other programs on your computer

Silencing your phone or placing it somewhere it will not be distracting

Testing that your audio is working and set to a comfortable volume that you can clearly hear

Not completing this experiment with others present




Please press the SPACE BAR to continue

You will watch 45 minutes of a crime mystery drama in which one character is suspected of having murdered another.


We will present background information about the characters of the show and the surrounding context before the episode begins.



Please press the SPACE BAR to continue

The video will intermittently pause while you watch to assess how certain you are that different characters in the show are guilty or innocent of having committed the murder.



Please press the SPACE BAR to continue

These certainty assessments tend to be flexible and may shift upon hearing something that a character says or seeing something that a character does or events that occur when a character is not on screen.


Some of this information may influence your assessments only slightly while other information may influence your assessments a great deal.


When prompted, please update your rating of how certain you are of each character's innocence or guilt at that moment in time.


Please try to be as precise as you can.



Please press the SPACE BAR to continue

These certainty assessments will be assessed on a continuous scale.


The scale ranges from 100% certain that a character is guilty to 100% certain that a character is innocent.


Leaving the scale in the middle (i.e., 0% certain) would indicate that you are completely uncertain whether a character is innocent or guilt.



Please press the SPACE BAR to continue

After your first rating, we will mark the scale where you had last rated that character to hopefully make updating your certainty rating easier.


A progress bar at the top will show the order in which you will assess the characters.


A portrait in the center of the screen will identify which character you are assessing at that moment.


Let's look at an example of what this looks like.



Please press the SPACE BAR to continue
